            "physical_description": "The tall, bulbous body resting on a circular base has a high waist, the top flared with an undulating rim, rising to meet the small curved spout at the font. The scroll handle of ebonised wood, swells in the middle and reduces towards the top which curves inwards.  It is attached to the body by a flared socket at the belly of the vessel.  The domed lid, detachable, rests inside the rim on an internal lip, has a moulded rim,a deep flange and is surmounted by a spherical, fluted finial of ebonised wood, attached by a screw thread through the top and retained by a circular nut.", 
